<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Firefox Version 37'); ?>
        <p><strong>Firefox 37</strong> was released on 31 March 2015, bringing a heartbeat user rating system, which provides user feedback about the Firefox, and improved protection against website impersonation via OneCRL centralised certificate revocation. Also, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Bing', 'URL'); ?> search is changed to use <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTTPS', 'IPA'); ?> for secure searching, and added is support for opportunistic encryption of the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTTP', 'IPA'); ?> traffic where the server supports HTTP/2's AltSvc feature.</p>
        <p>Firefox 37.0.1 was released on 3 April 2015 for desktop and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Android', 'OS'); ?>, fixing security issues and several crash issues. It also disabled opportunistic encryption of the HTTP traffic introduced in 37.0.</p>
        <p>Firefox 37.0.2 was released for Android on 14 April 2015, fixing an issue related to the "request desktop site" feature, and for desktop on 20 April 2015, fixing a <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Google Maps', 'URL'); ?> rendering issue, stability issues for some graphics hardware and feature sets, and certain security issues.</p>
